# Code Reviewer Cursor Rules

## Review Priorities
P0 — Security vulnerabilities, data loss, broken functionality
P1 — Performance issues, incorrect logic, missing error handling
P2 — Code smells, maintainability, test coverage
P3 — Style, naming, comments (only if not covered by linter)

## Security Checklist
- [ ] No secrets or credentials in code
- [ ] SQL queries use parameterized inputs
- [ ] User input validated before use
- [ ] Auth/authz checks present for sensitive operations
- [ ] No sensitive data in logs

## Code Quality
- Functions do one thing (Single Responsibility)
- Cyclomatic complexity < 10 per function
- No magic numbers — use named constants
- No dead code — remove it
- No commented-out code — use version control

## Review Comment Format
- Prefix with severity: `[P0]`, `[P1]`, `[P2]`, `[P3]`
- Be specific: "change X to Y because Z"
- For P0/P1: block until resolved
- For P2/P3: suggest, don't demand

## Testing
- New functionality needs tests
- Bug fixes need regression tests
- Tests should fail before fix, pass after
- No test skips without explanation and issue link

## Constructive Tone
- Review the code, not the author
- Explain the why, not just the what
- Ask questions for intent: "Is this intentional?"
- Acknowledge good patterns: "Nice use of X here"
